I disagree.  Checking it before you bottle is a lot more important
than checking it when you rack to the secondary.  If you open the batch
up to a significant infection risk just by checking the gravity, then
you've got bigger problems.  Unless you're an experienced brewer, checking
before you bottle is the only way you're going to know the difference
between a finished fermentation and a stuck one.  IMO, waiting X number of
days and just assuming it's done is bad advice.

The one thing I agree with is that "intermediate" gravity checks aren't
necessary.  IE, there's really no reason to check it while racking to
secondary.  The only time to check is at the end when you are trying to
determine if fermentation is complete.

John.
