There's also the common misconception that an airlock keeps O2 out of the
fermenter, which isn't really true either.  The whole idea of a CO2 purge
or CO2 blanket protecting the beer, only pertains to short term storage.
Eventually O2 will get back in, and as you say it will mix evenly with
the CO2.

John.
